{{Infobox book | name = The Encyclopedia of Punk | image = The Encyclopedia of Punk.jpg | image_size = 240px | caption = | author = Brian Cogan | title_orig = The Encyclopedia of Punk Music and Culture | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = [[English language|English]] | series = | subject = [[Punk music]] and [[Punk subculture|culture]] | genre = [[Reference book]] | publisher = Greenwood Press | pub_date = 2006 | english_pub_date = | media_type = | pages = | isbn = 978-0-313-33340-8 | oclc = 791194352 | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''The Encyclopedia of Punk''''' is a reference book about [[punk rock]] written by Brian Cogan,<ref name="Punk News Interview">{{cite web|last=Dauphin|first=Michael|title=Interviews: Brian Cogan (The Encyclopedia of Punk)|url=http://www.punknews.org/article/35197|publisher=Punk News|accessdate=22 January 2011}}</ref> an Associate Professor in the Department of Communications at [[Molloy College]] in [[Long Island, New York]].<ref name="Brian Cogan">{{cite web | url=https://journalism.nyu.edu/about-us/profile/brian-cogan/ | title=Brian Cogan | work=NYU Journalism|publisher=[[New York University]]| accessdate=July 21, 2017}}</ref> The book's original title was ''The Encyclopedia of punk music and culture''. The book traces the [[history of punk]] from its origins in the 1960s and 1970s to the present day.<ref>{{cite web|title=Encyclopedia of punk music and culture|url=http://newarrivals.nlb.gov.sg/itemdetail.aspx?bid=12758250|publisher=[[American Library Association]]|accessdate=22 January 2011}}</ref> A large part of the book is made up of rare photos of bands.<ref>{{cite web|title=the Encyclopedia of Punk|url=http://www.enjoy-your-style.com/encyclopedia-of-punk.html|publisher=Enjoy your style|accessdate=22 January 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Dale|first=Pete|title=Punk Record Labels and the Struggle for Autonomy: The Emergence of DIY. By Alan O'Connor. Plymouth: Lexington, 2008. 145 pp. {{ISBN|0-7391-2660-1}} Encyclopedia of Punk Music and Culture. By Brian Cogan. Westport, CT and London: Greenwood Press, 2006. 282 pp. {{ISBN|0-313-33340-8}}.|journal=Popular Music|year=2010|volume=29|pages=176–178|doi=10.1017/S0261143009990638}}</ref>
